Elliott ’92, President “HYMN TO AMHERST” Performed by the Amherst College Glee Club Led by Alexandra Conklin ’25 REMARKS Michael A. Elliott ’92, President READING OF GRADUATE NAMES Martha M. Umphrey, Provost and Dean of the Faculty Reception to follow at the Science Center Living Room HISTORY OF THE E CELEBRATION The E Celebration is an annual tradition at Amherst College that celebrates students who complete their degree requirements in the fall semester. For some, the E Celebration is a precursor to the Commencement events; for others, the event is the culmination of their years at Amherst College. At the E Celebration, each student receives a tassel and a 2026E Conway Cane.

data.title: How can something be so easy, yet so hard - Facebook
data.snippet: Inventing a smartphone is hard. Arguing is easy. Compromising is hard. Following rules is easy. Breaking rules and facing consequences are hard.
